sec.p:
The experimental set-up used for the stiffness testing (Fig. 4) is equipped with an actuator control unit specifically designed for artificially injecting hydraulic and electrical failures into the flight actuator, namely:


pressure loss of any of the two hydraulic supply lines (simulated by activating the related by-pass valve in the actuator manifold, Fig. 2);

open circuit of any of the four coils of the flight actuator servovalve;

short circuit of any of the four coils of the flight actuator servovalve.
